enhanced_by.reason: The 'increased' map is directly used in the 'isCoreChanged' method to determine if there are any changes.
The 'missing' map is directly used in the 'isCoreChanged' method to determine if there are any changes.
The 'changed' map is indirectly related to the 'isCoreChanged' method as it might affect the overall state of the headers.
The 'getIncreased' method is directly invoked in the 'isCoreChanged' method to check if there are any increased headers.
The 'getMissing' method is directly invoked in the 'isCoreChanged' method to check if there are any missing headers.
The 'RESPONSE_HEADERS_DECREASED.enabled' method is directly invoked in the 'isCoreChanged' method to check if the context allows decreased headers.
